Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economics Daleep Singh, Deputy Secretary of Commerce Don Graves, and Senior Advisor to the Secretary of State for Global Energy Security Amos Hochstein recently visited the United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia, and Qatar. The purpose of their trip was to discuss various economic matters such as trade, investment, infrastructure, climate change, and sustainability goals. They also explored opportunities for collaboration in clean energy and global infrastructure development. The delegation met with senior government officials in each country and agreed to continue the discussion on the topics addressed.